			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>You: </strong>An enthusiastic, energetic Web Application Developer eager to work in a &ldquo;full stack&rdquo; environment. What does this mean? Maybe you&rsquo;re comfortable in Python, but want to build something in Javascript using backbone.js. Or maybe you&rsquo;ve done a lot of &ldquo;front end&rdquo; work, but want to learn how to write efficient SQL queries on our PostgreSQL backend.</p>
<p>
<strong>Us: </strong>We&rsquo;re a Tokyo-based Internet startup helping large and small online services Go Global through our API and unique human translation platform. We love working with internationally-minded people, and most of our team have lived in another country before. A few even speak more than 3 languages. Perhaps because of all these languages we speak - and code in! - we&rsquo;re a tight-knit team that works hard, and has fun.</p>
<p>
<strong>Together: </strong>We will grow our API services (of which there will be many) into a platform capable of handling millions of translation jobs, worked on by tens of thousands of qualified translators. This includes everything from defining JSON payload formats, writing fast and furious SQL queries, and working closely in both front-end and server-side contexts. You will be the glue that ties an exciting platform together. And you will work with a team focused on working efficiently, together.</p>
<p>
You should have a firm grasp of API best-practices, perhaps have spec&#39;d and developed one yourself, and be comfortable in either Python or PHP. Through your deep knowledge of Open Source frameworks and libraries you also know when it&#39;s best to use a battle-tested tool instead of writing your own. You might have experience in building your own web-service or application, and thought about what happens if it ends up #1 on Hacker News (your service better stay up!). Sometimes you dream about how to solve the problem of thousands of users hitting the &ldquo;refresh&rdquo; button to load new data.<br />
<br />
If this sounds like fun, we&#39;d love to talk. This is an opportunity to work with some of the brightest engineers in Tokyo disrupting an industry that&#39;s ripe for innovation. We&#39;ve got several projects in the pipeline just waiting for someone to run with!</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Implement and guide application development, working closely with experienced full stack developers</li>
<li>
Maintain a performant application layer tightly coupled with our API</li>
<li>
Work with product managers and stakeholders to identify time tables and estimates for project completion; provide them with realistic expectations of what can and can&#39;t be done</li>
<li>
Pragmatically decide technologies and approaches without succumbing to NIH syndrome</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Understanding of APIs, HTTP headers, and JSON payload formats.</li>
<li>
Experience with technologies close to the &#39;server side&#39; of the web-stack, including Python and PostgreSQL</li>
<li>
Appreciation of the above, and experience with JavaScript and familiarity with JS frameworks such as Backbone.js, Spine.js, or AngularJS</li>
<li>
Experience with version control (Git or Mercurial, we use Git)</li>
<li>
Experience managing projects and facilitating communication between designers, developers, and product managers a plus</li>
<li>
Understanding of the differences between native XHR and JSON-P techniques for fetching data</li>
<li>
Interest in various cultures and languages; perhaps living outside your native country</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus skills:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
It&rsquo;s a bonus, but not required, to have experience in the following:</li>
<li>
Links to personal or open source project contributions</li>
<li>
Experience working with various databases, from Relational to NoSQL</li>
<li>
Experience building for a web-service in multiple localizations</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Competitive salary and benefits, related to experience</li>
<li>
Relocation package for candidates outside of Japan</li>
<li>
State-assisted health insurance as standard (Japan has one of the world&rsquo;s best healthcare systems)</li>
</ul>
